**** Pidgins -- Reduction in form
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ UP: <pidgin1>
Are they reduced in form?  see also red. of func. <pid-func> and red. of content {<inc> }

Having a reduced function, it only needs forms to meet the exigincies of the communication task at hand.  

--form of pidgin can stabilize
If a pidgin is in use in one area that has a continuous
influx of new speakers who need to acquire it as a
non-native language, then it will have a gretater chance of
stabilizing.  
